\par MILITARY SUPPORT TO CIVIL AUTHORITIES (MSCA)
\par 
\par }\pard \qj\widctlpar\adjustright {1.  }{\ul SITUATION:}{
  Emergency assistance to civilian communities may be necessary in the aftermath of a natural disaster.  Ellsworth AFB may be directed or requested to help in the recovery effort by providing resources and/or personnel.
\par 
\par 2.  }{\ul MISSION:}{  To support natural disaster relief operations in civilian communities upon direction of higher headquarters or request of the community.  Mission requirements will be considered when providing this assistance.
\par 
\par }\pard \qj\fi360\widctlpar\adjustright {a.  Forces Employed:
\par }\pard \qj\widctlpar\adjustright {
\par }\pard\plain \s17\qj\widctlpar\tx450\adjustright \fs20 {\tab \tab (1)  \tab AF National Security Emergency Prepa
redness Division (AFNSEP):  This agency directs and monitors Air Force resources used in natural disaster relief operations.  The division validates assistance requests and issues mission designators for official deployment of USAF assets.
\par }\pard\plain \qj\widctlpar\tx450\adjustright \fs20 {
\par }\pard\plain \s17\qj\widctlpar\tx450\adjustright \fs20 {\tab \tab (2)   The US Army Forces Command serves as the DoD Executive Agent for MSCA.
\par }\pard\plain \qj\widctlpar\tx450\adjustright \fs20 {
\par \tab b.  Assumptions:
\par 
\par \tab \tab (1)  \tab Air Force assistance will be provided only when the resources of city, county, and state governments have been exhausted.
\par 
\par \tab \tab (2)  \tab AFNSEP will direct Ellsworth AFB to support natural disaster relief operations within our area of responsibility.
\par 
\par \tab \tab (3) \tab Life-saving measures, property protection, and other actions to alleviate human suffering will be provided as directed by 28 BW/CC.
\par 
\par 3.  }{\ul EXECUTION: }{ 
\par 
\par \tab a.  Concept of Operations:
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s17\qj\widctlpar\tx450\adjustright \fs20 {\tab \tab 
(1)  The primary responsibility for minimizing the effects of a natural disaster rests with individuals, families, private industry, and local and state governments.  The American Red Cross and various other nonmilitary federal agencies may 
also be employed.\tab 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\widctlpar\tx450\adjustright \fs20 {
\par \tab \tab (2)  \tab Primary considerations must be to protect and restore essential mission assets, then assist local communities when directed or requested.  The resources committed to natural disaster relief operations must be consistent with def
ense priorities.
\par 
\par \tab \tab (3) \tab All support provided during natural disaster relief operations will be coordinated through the AF National Security Emergency Preparedness Division.  Any assistance rendered to a local community shall be on a cost reimbursable basi
s but assistance should not be delayed or denied in the absence of a reimbursable commitment.
\par 
\par \tab \tab (4) \tab Resources will be committed to off-base disaster operations only when civil resources are not adequate to cope with the situation and then only in minimum quantities.
\par 
\par \tab \tab (5)  \tab Air Force resources will not be used to restore or rehabilitate civil property or areas damaged or destroyed except when directed by the appropriate authority.
\par 
\par \tab b.  Tasks:  Actions are not necessarily sequential but all tasks must be considered.
